Some tips.

96
00:05:46.245 --> 00:05:50.553
Don't try to accomplish the work without first

97
00:05:50.553 --> 00:05:53.245
building relationships with the team.

98
00:05:53.245 --> 00:05:55.982
You've just been promoted, I know you have a lot on your plate,

99
00:05:55.982 --> 00:05:57.598
but be patient, speak with everyone individually,

100
00:05:57.598 --> 00:06:01.127
and as a group, understand the group, understand the issues,

101
00:06:01.127 --> 00:06:07.245
and understand the work that's on the table from their viewpoint.

102
00:06:07.245 --> 00:06:11.245
Don't assume that your team members understand how you or others work.

103
00:06:11.245 --> 00:06:16.245
Take the time to explain processes and your expectations.

104
00:06:16.245 --> 00:06:19.322
When they understand your expectations,

105
00:06:19.322 --> 00:06:24.245
that helps drive quality work towards your goals.

106
00:06:24.245 --> 00:06:27.245
Don't be afraid to communicate early on and repeatedly.

107
00:06:27.245 --> 00:06:32.245
You do not want your team to be unsure, lost or confused, or not listened to.

108
00:06:32.245 --> 00:06:36.134
What you don't want to hear from your team is, what is he doing?

109
00:06:36.134 --> 00:06:37.245
What does she think?

110
00:06:37.245 --> 00:06:42.456
You want to make sure that that's very clear about who

111
00:06:42.456 --> 00:06:46.245
you are and what you're trying to do.

